  <description type="morphology">Leaves 2–3 mm; margins entire; costa 155–180 µm wide; basal laminal cells 19–55 × 4–19 µm, narrower at margins; distal laminal cells 24–55 × 3–7 µm.  Specialized asexual reproduction by clusters of spindle-shaped brood leaves in the comal tufts.  Sporophytes not found in North America.</description>
